the values of W evaluated using both kinds of ï¬tting for VZrF6 are almost the same negative value of âˆ’10 K,
indicating small antiferromagnetic interactions. Electron conï¬gurations of Ti2+ and V2+ are t22g and t23g, respectively. In the crystal structure, nearest neighboring transition metal

ions interact through their t2g orbitals. Although the distance between two magnetic ions is relatively large, kinetic

exchange interactions through t2g orbitals are likely to be the origin of antiferromagnetic interactions in TiZrF6 and VZrF6. Since, they show no sign of magnetic ordering down to 2 K, the frustration indices f Â¼ jWj=TN of Ti and V compounds are f > 27 and 5, respectively.

