The lower panel of Fig. 4 shows magnetic entropy, which
is obtained by integrating Cm=T. At low temperatures, S decreases with applying magnetic ï¬eld owing to the
increasement of Zeeman splitting. The magnetic entropy under each ï¬eld is close to R ln 2 at 40 K rather than R ln 4. Magnetic entropy also indicates that Co2+ is not in a spin state of S Â¼ 3=2 but in a ï¬ctitious spin state of Jeï¬€ Â¼ 1=2.
